				<p><p>Neural networks are not the best by a loooong shot. Neural networks are <em>not</em> AI, they are a way to do regression and classification. If you don't know what those things are, then you have no business working with Neural Networks.</p>

<p>What you have described is a mapping problem. You need two things from a good algorithm in this case:</p>

<ol>
<li><p>Coverage. You need to ensure that the robot can reach every part of the maze. If it cannot, then it might not find the exit / entrance.</p></li>
<li><p>Mapping. You need to ensure that you can keep track of all the obstacles.</p></li>
</ol>

<p>Without more information about the type of maze, type of robot, and type of obstacles, I'm afraid this problem is under-determined. </p>
</p><br>
